  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the iron teppan to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Mix the Canadian Stilton cheese with 2 tablespoons of softened butter, until well combined.",
    "Grate the 3 cloves of garlic and add to the cheese mixture.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix the honey, brown sugar, flour, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Pour the honey mixture over the cheese mixture and mix until smooth.",
    "Transfer the cheese mixture to a greased iron teppan and smooth out the top.",
    "Bake for 12 minutes or until the glaze is golden brown.",
    "Let it rest for 2 minutes before serving."
  ],
